      prompt: `<div>In the xy-plane, an equation of circle R is (x + 7)<sup>2</sup> + (y + 19)<sup>2</sup> = 100. Circle S is obtained by shifting circle R to the right 2 units. An equation defining circle S is (x + h)<sup>2</sup> + (y + k)<sup>2</sup> = 100, where h and k are constants. What is the value of h?</div>`,
